Hi Floby Team,

I hope you're doing well. I wanted to give you a heads-up regarding a configuration issue on our Ignition Gateway (flosvl1024.flo.volvocars.net) and the planned resolution.

**What Happened**
While setting up access restrictions for a new user/role on the Ignition Gateway, I accidentally modified the Config and Status section permissions in General Settings. As a result, the IgnitionAdmin account currently cannot access the Config and Status pages on the Gateway Webpage (port 8088).

**Impact Assessment**
I want to reassure you that this issue has NO impact on the following:

- ✅ All running projects — fully operational
- ✅ Designer access — you can continue working normally
- ✅ Tags, OPC UA connections, and data pipelines — unaffected
- ✅ Alarms and historians — running as expected
- ✅ All existing user configurations — unchanged

The issue is isolated to the Gateway Webpage Config/Status section access for IgnitionAdmin only.

**Planned Fix**
We have identified the exact fix — a targeted update to the gateway configuration database (config.idb) to restore the correct permission settings. The fix itself takes less than 2 minutes.

However, to apply the change safely, we will need to restart the Ignition Gateway service, which will cause approximately 1-2 minutes of downtime. During this time:
- Designer sessions will briefly disconnect and auto-reconnect
- Projects will resume automatically after restart.
- No data loss will occur
